reviews.review_text: Best sounding source Go figure. The least d-loaded source, out of eight, sounds the best. I like this better than the Wagner, Miller version. This Nak 300 version has more warmth and balance. Less fatiguing on the ears. The performance, as stated by others, is one of the years finest. I also like, the 300 source for the 11th, the best.
- I have to agree. Miller's been trumped on this one. Not that I really oughta be keeping score or anything, but yeah, this sounds nice.

Great Fire solos.... Love this show and this source has the clearest sound. 

Highlights are the Fire solos and the NFA...just exactly perfect.  Lots of other great Jerry moments - try it out!

My fav Of all of the Dead shows I ever attended (admittedly fewer than 30) this is my favorite. It was a beautiful Saturday night at one of my favorite venues, the Greek Theater in Berkeley. You could go up top and see the sun set over the Golden Gate bridge. There is a low ledge along the wall that separates the inner part from the seats above that you could sit on before the show and during the break and then stand and dance on during the show, that was both close to the stage and with room to really move around and dance. The music was so great, with a exceptional set list, an amazing Its All Over Now Baby Blue encore, and then my first ever 2nd encore! A brilliant evening!
